modules.description: Handles parsing and retrieval of boot-time parameters passed from Solo5 to MirageOS. Operates on string-based key-value pairs and provides functions to extract specific values as integers, strings, or lists. Used to configure network interfaces, set boot flags, and pass runtime parameters to unikernels.

Returns a lazy, asynchronous representation of the command-line arguments. Operates on string arrays and Lwt promises to handle environment variables. Useful for delaying argument retrieval until needed in event-driven applications.
